  "doc_id": "42071",
  "text": "Human vision is a complicated binocular process. Among others, it involves stereopsis, which is the parallax provided by the two eyes' different positions on the head giving precise depth perception [CITATION_1] , and binocular fusion typified by the visualization of a single image despite each eye having its image of any object [CITATION_2] . Another vital feature is a binocular summation, which is an enhanced ability to detect faint objects [CITATION_3] compared to monocular vision.",
